==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Michaelmas
<hw>Mich"ael*mas</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Michael</ets> + <ets>mass</ets> religious service; OE.
<ets>Mighelmesse</ets>.]</ety> <def>The feast of the archangel Michael,
a church festival, celebrated on the 29th of September. Hence,
colloquially, autumn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Michaelmas daisy</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See
under <er>Daisy</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Michelangelesque</ent>⟦br⟧
